Hello! This is my custom configuration of my Corne V4.1 (46 keys) for QMK.
Because of my specific Linux distro, I needed to write a custom loader for the
keyboard device. Mostly because the Redhat cuck-ware; udev, does not work.

I've set this up for portability. Please read the Makefile for more
information!.

  File:         | Description:
.---------------+---------------------------------------- - -  - .
|-- Makefile    | Contains recipes for custom mounting and compilation
|-- README      |
|-- config.h    | Basic config options.
|-- default.vil | The same config (older) for VIAL.
|-- keymap.c    | Keymaps file, contains the three main layers.
|-- rules.mk    | Basic(er) config options.
`-- x3hy -> ~/qmk_firmware/keyboards/crkbd/keymaps/x3hy
            ^ run: $ make keymap
